      "content": "i was looking at some old maps of dc last night and something weird caught my eye. if you look at how the major avenues intersect with the memorial sites, it's not just random planning. the geometry is way too precise. it looks like a pattern, almost like a sigil or a ritual layout. have u ever seen anything like that in urban planning?",
